  "texts": [
    "Fig. 2 The GPS' contribution to the task of 'spatial orientation' can be substitutive at the highest level and constitutive at a lower level for a specific sub-task of 'reading text'",
    "• Substitutive-EXT: an extended cognitive system that performs at least the extended cognitive process X in such a way that 1) the agent performs only a minimal degree of brain-based cognitive agency for performing the cognitive process X, using the technological resource for performing most of the cognitive work necessary for X.",
    "2) the agent can perform and display the brain-based cognitive process X independently of the artifact's contribution. 11",
    "Although Pritchard's framework offers useful insights, given the limitations expressed in the previous section it is not sufficient for addressing the TET.",
    "First, we need a framework applicable to all conditions: those in which EXT criteria are met and those in which are not."
